copy
-----
syn: cp source_filename destination_filename

ex: cp file dir1

copies file1 in directory 1

ex: cp -r dira dirb

to copy a directory in another directory we should use recursive

its like copy and paste in windows

move
______

SYNTAX  mv source_file destination_file
------
 
 ex: mv file1 file2
 
 its like cut and paste in windows

 rename
 --------
for rename also we use mv only 

mv old_name new_name

remove files/directories
-----------------------

rm filename

rmdir dirname

rm -rf file/directory

tree
-----
tree is the command works like ls only but tree gives you the clear picture 
